text: Hakim El Mokeddem (born 15 February 1999) is a French professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for FC Sète 34, on loan from Stade Rennais. ==Club career== El Mokeddem made his professional debut in a 1–1 Ligue 1 tie with AS Monaco FC on 15 September 2018. Having spent the 2019–20 season on loan at Stade Lavallois, he moved to FC Sète 34 on loan for the 2020–21 season in September 2020. ==International career== Born in France, El Mokeddem is of Algerian descent. El Mokeddem is a youth international for France.
